  <span id="freeText11131926946583783455" style="display:none">I read Bartleby years ago. I read it again recently. I still don't know what to make of it in a logical sense, but it speaks very deeply to something inside of me. What that something is, I may never know, but I do know that the book will stay with me for as long as I'm around. <br /><br />Is there a Bartleby somewhere in each of us?</span>
