  <span id="freeText13404257354912446212" style="display:none">Oh, Bartleby! will you not oblige me with your trying to be a bit alike dear senor Jose in <b>
  <i>All the names</i>
</b> by my beloved Jose Saramago? I would be very desirous to see you in that manner. Yet, how well I know by now that you <b>
  <i>would prefer not to</i>
</b>. And yes, every eye is upon you with the expectation of an example, because you were truly at liberty to pursue your own methods! You are so steady, so uniform in your conduct, so willing of sliding through life to the end of it unnoted, and not wishing to be observed even for your silent motion, sufficiently content in the consciousness of rather useful than glaring. But, guess what? To your regret, you were pushed into blaze!</span>
